50|$|<b>Suspension</b> <b>forks</b> {{have become}} {{increasingly}} sophisticated. The amount of travel available has typically increased. When <b>suspension</b> <b>forks</b> were introduced, 80-100 mm of travel was deemed sufficient for a downhill mountain bike. This amount of travel is now common for cross-country disciplines, whereas downhill forks typically offer 200 mm of travel for handling the most extreme terrain.|$|R
